## ğŸš€ Features

- ğŸ§¾ Automatic route-to-template mapping  
- ğŸ’¡ Clean, Mako-based templating with inheritance and Python expressions  
- ğŸ” Request and response objects available in templates  
- ğŸ”§ Custom application context injection  
- ğŸ“„ Built-in 404 template support  

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Usage


### Example Template (`index.template`)

```mako
<%! from datetime import datetime %>
<h1>${APP_NAME}</h1>
<p>Current time: ${datetime.now()}</p>
<p>Request method: ${request.method}</p>
```

```bash
pip install renderly
```

In `run.py`:

```python
from renderly import App

application = App(name="Renderly Demo", project_dir="templates")
```
## Run with uwsgi

```bash
uwsgi --http :8000 --wsgi-file run.py --callable application
```


---

## ğŸ“¦ App Context

You can pass global values into templates via `app_context`:

```python
App(name="Renderly", app_context={"version": "1.0"})
```

Then use `${version}` in your templates.

---

## âš ï¸ 404 Handling

If a requested template doesnâ€™t exist, Renderly will render the fallback file (default: `404.template`).

